  "title": "Carpenter Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /><br />- Oversee the entire carpentry production process, from material procurement to finished product.<br />- Develop and implement production schedules and ensure they are met.<br />- Supervise carpentry teams, assigning tasks and monitoring performance.<br />- Ensure that all carpentry work meets quality standards and specifications.<br />- Enforce and maintain safety protocols and ensure the proper use of personal protective equipment.<br />- Manage and maintain tools, equipment, and machinery.<br />- Optimise production processes to improve efficiency and reduce waste.</p><p><strong>Material Management:</strong><br /><br />- Oversee the procurement and storage of carpentry materials.<br />- Manage inventory levels and ensure materials are readily available.<br />- Coordinate with suppliers to ensure timely delivery of materials.</p><p><strong>Skills and Qualifications:</strong></p><p>- Diploma/Degree or practical experience in carpenter management.<br />- Technical expertise and strong knowledge of carpentry techniques, materials, and tools.<br />- Ability to lead and motivate a team, delegate tasks, and resolve production issues and quality problems.<br />- Ability to identify, plan and manage production schedules and materials processes.</p>",
